3 changes to the spec:
1) the colour when a car is paused/stopped should be something highly visible (not grey) to highlight a hold up.
2) the egress routes are not as clearly defined. Given the egress from the school is in Aristea Rd. the likely route out is likely via Childrens Way / Ladies Mile or Dreysersdal / Main Rd. The traffic via Homestead / ladies Mile and Dreysdal / Firgrove will be compounded by Sweet Valley school traffic and will most likely be chaotic. But sinc ewe dont have the Sweet Valley traffic data, it is hard to model these 2 exits diffently.
3) i dont really want all the junction points visible. they must be there for the simulation, but just not show. perhaps the ones with the controlled stops or all-stops, and the new traffic calming measure and the ingress / egress at the school. Keep these juntions: 7, 20, 6, 5, 4, 18, 28, 10, 13, 9, 8, 1. the label should just state the junction between the roads, and the control measure.



- i am still not happy with the school drop off. The egress road from teh school entrance to the exit is no longer visible. it used to be a grey dotted line. Then it is along this line that parent will drop off there kids. So these things will need to be modelled:
1) delay to enter the school gate if there is traffic at the ingress.
2) 20km/h speed while on the grey school rd
3) there are drop off parking all along the grey line. however, once those are full, cars will wait for free spots and start to block the ingress/egress rd.
4) 45s delay for drop off
5) Ruskin and Aristea will need to be an appropriate speed for around a school, but likely below 60km/h
6) The following information must be part of the calculation:
    - Inside school grounds (on-site): 98 bays
    - Outside on Ruskin Road (on-street): 22 bays
 the stop-and-drop rate is calculated at 1 bay per 20 learners for 1,120 learners — that's a 56-bay drop-off requirement just for the stop-and-drop facility. plot this along the grey school line
 7) the outside bays can be used for drop and go too and needs to be modelled on Ruskin Rd and its impact on the traffic.
 
